window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>An ex-cop who cannot die. A moon full of settlers who cannot thrive. </b></p> <p>Mahina's terraformers built a high-tech urban paradise. Then Earth flooded the colony with desperate refugees, cop Sass Collier among them.</p> <p>The settlers who arrived with Sass died decades ago. Outside the citadel, their descendants die weak and young.</p> <p>Sass fought a rebellion against the city once. She won concessions to give the settlers a chance at health. She paid with 20 years in prison.</p> <p>Now she’s out, a reformed character. She assembles an oddball crew doing odd jobs. She intends to mind her own business–how to make a profit on the skyship <i>Thrive.</i></p> <p>But her fellow settlers are still failing.</p> <p>While her business model careens toward circus acts, Sass dares to defy the city again, to solve Mahina’s failure to thrive.</p> <p>Pick up <b><i>Thrive</i></b> because you love upbeat character-driven SF with fun technology. Suggested for fans of <i>Firefly</i>, Lindsay Buroker's <i>Star Kingdom</i>, or Nathan Lowell’s <i>Golden Age of the Solar Clipper</i> books.</p> <p>This <b>Publisher's Pack</b> includes <i>Skyship Thrive</i> and <i>Spaceship Thrive</i>.</p>"; 
